00:57:37.232 --> 00:57:41.110
Well, uh... I learned how
to make meat pies tonight.


1205
00:57:41.152 --> 00:57:42.779
That's a first.

1206
00:57:42.821 --> 00:57:44.656
And I'm heading back
to the cottage


1207
00:57:44.697 --> 00:57:46.950
to write my article.

1208
00:57:46.991 --> 00:57:48.159
Hey, um...

1209
00:57:49.828 --> 00:57:51.496
why did Everett leave?

1210
00:57:51.538 --> 00:57:53.957
Campbell, you know this.

1211
00:57:53.998 --> 00:57:55.083
Yeah, sure.

1212
00:57:55.124 --> 00:57:56.292
Uh, just...

1213
00:57:56.334 --> 00:57:58.211
just walk me through it.

1214
00:57:58.253 --> 00:57:59.796
<i>We were young</i>

1215
00:57:59.838 --> 00:58:02.674
and Everett wasn't ready
to be a father.


1216
00:58:02.715 --> 00:58:05.301
I mean, I wasn't ready
to be a mother either,


1217
00:58:05.343 --> 00:58:06.928
but it just hit him hard,

1218
00:58:06.970 --> 00:58:09.222
<i>and when you were two,
he lost his job,</i>


1219
00:58:09.264 --> 00:58:11.266
<i>and he was a wreck.</i>

1220
00:58:11.307 --> 00:58:14.102
Anyway, after he left,

1221
00:58:14.143 --> 00:58:16.521
<i>it was just like
he didn't want to be found.</i>


1222
00:58:16.563 --> 00:58:18.690
<i>So I stopped trying.</i>

1223
00:58:18.731 --> 00:58:22.944
You don't think maybe
he wanted to come back?


1224
00:58:22.986 --> 00:58:25.780
Well, if he wanted to come back,
he would have.


1225
00:58:25.822 --> 00:58:27.782
<i>Why? Did he say something?</i>

1226
00:58:27.824 --> 00:58:31.870
No. No, not officially.

1227
00:58:31.911 --> 00:58:34.789
I'm still trying
to get the truth out of him.


1228
00:58:34.831 --> 00:58:38.293
- You want my two cents?
- Sure.


1229
00:58:38.334 --> 00:58:40.962
<i>He's never going to spill
his guts to a journalist,</i>


1230
00:58:41.004 --> 00:58:45.175
<i>but he might tell his daughter
everything she wants to know.</i>


1231
00:58:45.216 --> 00:58:47.677
Oh, I forgot my camera
back at the house.


1232
00:58:47.719 --> 00:58:49.804
Can I call you back?

1233
00:58:49.846 --> 00:58:53.516
- Sure. Love you.
- I love you too.


1234
00:58:53.558 --> 00:58:57.353
Everett, wait, wait!

1235
00:58:57.395 --> 00:58:59.606
Everett, just talk to me!

1236
00:58:59.647 --> 00:59:02.150
Talk to me.

1237
00:59:02.192 --> 00:59:05.320
Jennifer, I know that your heart
is in the right place,


1238
00:59:05.361 --> 00:59:09.741
but having Campbell here digging
into my past, it's too much.


1239
00:59:09.782 --> 00:59:11.701
Okay, yes.
I'm sorry, I really am.


1240
00:59:11.743 --> 00:59:15.038
But maybe it's a good thing?
It could be cathartic.


1241
00:59:15.079 --> 00:59:17.540
Look, I'm only trying
to do what's best for you.


1242
00:59:17.582 --> 00:59:18.875
I know.

1243
00:59:18.917 --> 00:59:22.003
I know, and...
I love you for it.


1244
00:59:25.673 --> 00:59:28.551
I ever tell you about
the last time I saw her?


1245
00:59:28.593 --> 00:59:30.637
No.

1246
00:59:30.678 --> 00:59:32.555
After I was away
for a few years,


1247
00:59:32.597 --> 00:59:34.224
I started to think,

1248
00:59:34.265 --> 00:59:37.227
I'm on my way to being
a better man, better father,


1249
00:59:37.268 --> 00:59:39.896
so I thought,
well, I should look her up.


1250
00:59:39.938 --> 00:59:43.608
So I researched Alice's school,
and it turns out


1251
00:59:43.650 --> 00:59:46.611
they're having
a Christmas pageant.


1252
00:59:46.653 --> 00:59:50.990
I thought, well,
that's the perfect time.


1253
00:59:51.032 --> 00:59:53.076
So I drove back to Texas
all night


1254
00:59:53.117 --> 00:59:55.370
and I stood in the back
of the auditorium and...


1255
00:59:55.411 --> 00:59:58.248
I watched the whole thing.

1256
00:59:58.289 --> 01:00:00.208
And...

1257
01:00:00.250 --> 01:00:05.004
she was just the cutest thing
you've ever seen.


1258
01:00:05.046 --> 01:00:06.926
So after the show,
I thought I'd go talk to her,


1259
01:00:06.965 --> 01:00:09.509
but her... her mom
and this other man


1260
01:00:09.551 --> 01:00:12.303
get their first,

1261
01:00:12.345 --> 01:00:15.014
and he gives her roses

1262
01:00:15.056 --> 01:00:16.933
and she jumps into his arms.

1263
01:00:18.434 --> 01:00:20.311
They were so happy, Jennifer.

1264
01:00:22.438 --> 01:00:24.941
It was...

1265
01:00:26.025 --> 01:00:28.862
it was the perfect family.

1266
01:00:28.903 --> 01:00:31.114
Then what happened?

1267
01:00:31.156 --> 01:00:33.074
I left.

1268
01:00:34.993 --> 01:00:36.578
But I never stopped loving her.

1269
01:00:38.746 --> 01:00:42.041
Even if I have to love her
from a distance...


1270
01:00:45.086 --> 01:00:47.547
she'll always be right here.

1271
01:00:49.549 --> 01:00:51.467
<i>♪ Christmas lights</i>

1272
01:00:51.509 --> 01:00:53.845
<i>♪ See them shine</i>

1273
01:00:53.887 --> 01:00:56.264
<i>♪ In the eyes</i>

1274
01:00:56.306 --> 01:00:58.474
<i>♪ Of a child</i>

1275
01:01:00.518 --> 01:01:03.188
<i>♪ Let them shine</i>

1276
01:01:40.225 --> 01:01:42.644
Hi, merry Christmas Eve.
What can I get you?


1277
01:01:54.197 --> 01:01:55.865
How are my two
favorite tastemakers?


1278
01:01:55.907 --> 01:01:57.450
Hungry.

1279
01:01:57.492 --> 01:01:59.536
You're awfully quiet.
What's up?


1280
01:01:59.577 --> 01:02:01.329
Just...

1281
01:02:01.371 --> 01:02:04.624
when tonight is over,
you've got to go home, right?


1282
01:02:04.666 --> 01:02:07.293
Well, she has work, Amelia. She
can't just stay here forever.


1283
01:02:07.335 --> 01:02:09.045
Well, I know that, but...

1284
01:02:09.087 --> 01:02:11.881
Well, that doesn't mean
I'm leaving, not really.


1285
01:02:11.923 --> 01:02:14.384
I mean, we still
have Christmas breakfast,


1286
01:02:14.425 --> 01:02:17.136
and then we can
video-chat and text,


1287
01:02:17.178 --> 01:02:19.347
and I'm only
an hour away by plane.


1288
01:02:19.389 --> 01:02:22.016
So... I can come back
and visit.


1289
01:02:22.058 --> 01:02:23.351
- You promise?
- Yeah.


1290
01:02:23.393 --> 01:02:25.478
- You'll come back?
- I promise.


1291
01:02:25.520 --> 01:02:27.188
In the meantime,

1292
01:02:27.230 --> 01:02:29.899
I have a very important
mission for you guys.


1293
01:02:29.941 --> 01:02:33.027
I need to go help your mom with
my new skills in the truck,


1294
01:02:33.069 --> 01:02:35.572
and I need someone to go around
and take some pictures


1295
01:02:35.613 --> 01:02:37.115
for my article.

1296
01:02:37.157 --> 01:02:38.950
Are you guys up for it?

1297
01:02:38.992 --> 01:02:40.618
- Wait, for real?
- Yeah.


1298
01:02:40.660 --> 01:02:43.329
- You can count on us.
- Okay, good. Here. Be careful.


1299
01:02:43.371 --> 01:02:45.373
- Yes!
- -Come on, Mary-Margaret.


1300
01:02:45.415 --> 01:02:50.545
Here. And needless to say,
he never went caroling again.


1301
01:02:55.300 --> 01:02:56.593
Everything all right, there?

1302
01:02:56.634 --> 01:02:59.804
Um, yeah. I'm just, um...

1303
01:02:59.846 --> 01:03:00.930
just thinking.

1304
01:03:00.972 --> 01:03:03.016
Anything I can help with?

1305
01:03:03.057 --> 01:03:05.685
Not unless, uh, you know
how to tell the man


1306
01:03:05.727 --> 01:03:09.314
you're writing a story about
that you're his daughter.


1307
01:03:09.355 --> 01:03:11.316
You're gonna tell him?

1308
01:03:11.357 --> 01:03:13.359
Yeah, it's, uh... it's time.

1309
01:03:16.321 --> 01:03:19.407
I don't know why
you did it, you know,


1310
01:03:19.449 --> 01:03:23.828
uh, finding me, and, uh,
asking me here


1311
01:03:23.870 --> 01:03:25.705
and helping me through the week.

1312
01:03:25.747 --> 01:03:26.915
But, um...

1313
01:03:26.956 --> 01:03:29.209
thank you...

1314
01:03:29.250 --> 01:03:31.961
from the bottom of my heart.

1315
01:03:32.003 --> 01:03:34.088
Well, you know,
you don't need a reason


1316
01:03:34.130 --> 01:03:37.133
to bring more love
into the world.


1317
01:03:37.175 --> 01:03:39.594
Ladies, we're out of meat pies.
Need some more.


1318
01:03:39.636 --> 01:03:42.931
Excuse you, we were having
a moment here.


1319
01:03:42.972 --> 01:03:45.183
You know what?

1320
01:03:45.225 --> 01:03:48.394
Why don't you take it easy,
go walk around the party,


1321
01:03:48.436 --> 01:03:50.063
and I can handle things here?

1322
01:03:50.104 --> 01:03:51.773
Okay.

1323
01:03:51.814 --> 01:03:54.400
Have fun.

1324
01:03:54.442 --> 01:03:55.235
Thank you.

1325
01:03:55.276 --> 01:03:56.736
You're welcome.

1326
01:04:14.045 --> 01:04:16.297
All right, so,
what are you going to tell him?


1327
01:04:16.339 --> 01:04:17.966
You are just as bad as Jennifer.

1328
01:04:18.007 --> 01:04:20.718
- It's a big moment, Campbell.
- I know it's a big moment.


1329
01:04:20.760 --> 01:04:23.405
I'm trying not to freak out, and
the two of you are making it worse.


1330
01:04:23.429 --> 01:04:25.324
Ah, so what you're saying is,
you need a distraction.


1331
01:04:25.348 --> 01:04:26.808
- Yes, please.
- Hmm.


1332
01:04:26.850 --> 01:04:28.852
Do you know how to two-step?

1333
01:04:30.395 --> 01:04:32.689
- No?
- No.


1334
01:04:34.190 --> 01:04:35.316
- Really good.
- Yeah.


1335
01:04:38.653 --> 01:04:40.488
Oh, wow, you think
you're really smooth, huh?


1336
01:04:40.530 --> 01:04:42.758
I promise you I did not know
it was going to be a slow song.


1337
01:04:42.782 --> 01:04:45.201
- I am so sorry.
- So, you don't want to dance?


1338
01:04:45.243 --> 01:04:48.204
- No, I didn't say that.
- I'm messing with you, Jackson.


1339
01:04:50.957 --> 01:04:52.208
Take my hand.

1340
01:04:55.837 --> 01:04:58.423
Never had a Christmas quite
like this one, I must say.


1341
01:04:58.464 --> 01:05:00.216
Yeah?
Where was your last one?


1342
01:05:00.258 --> 01:05:04.596
Uh, I was about a hundred miles
outside of Ulaanbaatar,


1343
01:05:04.637 --> 01:05:06.681
learning how
the Mongolian herders


1344
01:05:06.723 --> 01:05:09.309
keep their animals alive
during the winter.


1345
01:05:09.350 --> 01:05:12.645
- So a very normal one.
- Yes, yes. Mm-hmm.


1346
01:05:12.687 --> 01:05:15.607
Don't worry,
this one is... much better.


1347
01:05:18.818 --> 01:05:23.031
Yeah, way less chance
of frostbite here.


1348
01:05:23.072 --> 01:05:24.491
I'm pretty sure
I read every book


1349
01:05:24.532 --> 01:05:27.076
on the outside world
past the parish lines,


1350
01:05:27.118 --> 01:05:29.078
and I've never been past them.

1351
01:05:29.120 --> 01:05:31.247
I can't believe that. How?

1352
01:05:31.289 --> 01:05:33.041
My family's been here
for generations.


1353
01:05:33.082 --> 01:05:34.709
My parents had me later in life,

1354
01:05:34.751 --> 01:05:36.669
and I'm pretty sure
they don't want me to leave.


1355
01:05:36.711 --> 01:05:40.089
- Hmm.
- Follow in the old family footsteps.


1356
01:05:40.131 --> 01:05:43.551
Become Pere Noel,
work for the city.


1357
01:05:43.593 --> 01:05:46.387
Settle down, essentially do
everything that they did.


1358
01:05:46.429 --> 01:05:50.433
I mean, I know
it's none of my business,


1359
01:05:50.475 --> 01:05:54.103
but I think your family
would want you to be happy


1360
01:05:54.145 --> 01:05:56.856
and leave Sorrento,
if that's what you want,


1361
01:05:56.898 --> 01:05:58.942
you know, see the world
outside of your books.


1362
01:05:58.983 --> 01:06:00.944
Yeah. Maybe.

1363
01:06:02.904 --> 01:06:05.990
So, okay, where would you go
if you could be anywhere?


1364
01:06:06.032 --> 01:06:07.951
That's a very good question.

1365
01:06:07.992 --> 01:06:09.577
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.


1366
01:06:09.619 --> 01:06:11.412
Um...

1367
01:06:11.454 --> 01:06:12.997
Where are <i>you</i> going next?

1368
01:06:14.916 --> 01:06:16.709
Um...

1369
01:06:16.751 --> 01:06:19.087
my editor was talking
about me doing a story


1370
01:06:19.128 --> 01:06:21.214
in Morocco.

1371
01:06:21.256 --> 01:06:23.800
- Morocco?
- Mm-hmm.


1372
01:06:23.842 --> 01:06:25.885
That's where I want to go.

1373
01:06:41.568 --> 01:06:43.361
Campbell, come on!

1374
01:06:43.403 --> 01:06:45.905
Oh, it's starting.

1375
01:06:45.947 --> 01:06:47.657
Are you coming?

1376
01:07:07.051 --> 01:07:08.761
Merry Christmas, everybody!

1377
01:07:08.803 --> 01:07:10.638
Merry Christmas!

1378
01:07:10.680 --> 01:07:13.391
Now, you know I'm not
one for big speeches.


1379
01:07:13.433 --> 01:07:15.977
It occurred to me that Christmas

1380
01:07:16.019 --> 01:07:19.898
happens during the darkest
and coldest time of the year.


1381
01:07:19.939 --> 01:07:22.650
And here in Louisiana,
that's about 50 degrees.


1382
01:07:24.360 --> 01:07:26.321
But with our care
for each other,


1383
01:07:26.362 --> 01:07:28.364
we cast off that chill.

1384
01:07:28.406 --> 01:07:34.412
We illuminate the darkness
with fire and celebration.


1385
01:07:34.454 --> 01:07:38.333
So it's only fitting
that we would ask the family


1386
01:07:38.374 --> 01:07:43.046
of our newest Pere Noel,
Everett Bergeron,


1387
01:07:43.087 --> 01:07:45.465
to join us in the tradition

1388
01:07:45.507 --> 01:07:48.051
of calling out
the Christmas alligators


1389
01:07:48.092 --> 01:07:51.679
to welcome him back to Sorrento
and kick off Christmas.


1390
01:07:51.721 --> 01:07:53.723
Ladies, please.

1391
01:07:56.559 --> 01:07:58.811
Come on.
Come on.


1392
01:07:58.853 --> 01:08:00.522
Yeah. Okay.

1393
01:08:00.563 --> 01:08:02.690
- Wait, what is it again?
- It's like the book.


1394
01:08:02.732 --> 01:08:05.360
- Oh! Okay. Okay, okay, okay.
- You girls ready?


1395
01:08:05.401 --> 01:08:07.278
- Yes.
- All right, here we go.


1396
01:08:07.320 --> 01:08:08.905
Ha, Gaston!

1397
01:08:08.947 --> 01:08:10.323
Ha, Tiboy!

1398
01:08:10.365 --> 01:08:12.116
Ha, Pierre an' Alcee'!

1399
01:08:12.158 --> 01:08:13.493
Gee, Ninette!

1400
01:08:13.535 --> 01:08:15.453
Gee, Suzette!

1401
01:08:15.495 --> 01:08:17.705
Celeste an' Renee!

1402
01:08:17.747 --> 01:08:20.208
<i>Allons-y!</i>

1403
01:08:43.398 --> 01:08:44.941
There it is!

1404
01:08:50.321 --> 01:08:52.157
Merry Christmas, y'all!

1405
01:08:52.198 --> 01:08:54.367
Merry Christmas!

1406
01:08:57.203 --> 01:08:58.955
Happy holidays!

1407
01:08:58.997 --> 01:09:01.833
Yohhhh!

1408
01:09:07.964 --> 01:09:09.966
Ho ho ho!

1409
01:09:14.470 --> 01:09:16.181
Merry Christmas, y'all!

1410
01:09:16.222 --> 01:09:18.850
Merry Christmas!

1411
01:09:21.269 --> 01:09:23.688
Hey-hey! Hey there, my girls!

1412
01:09:23.730 --> 01:09:25.023
Merry Christmas.

1413
01:09:25.064 --> 01:09:27.734
Some candy canes
for my favorite girls.


1414
01:09:27.775 --> 01:09:30.403
That's right, let's get
this Christmas party started!


1415
01:09:36.284 --> 01:09:39.204
This time of night
it's customary for Pere Noel


1416
01:09:39.245 --> 01:09:41.206
to make a little toast.

1417
01:09:41.247 --> 01:09:44.375
I'm sure Mayor Thomas has
already given a fine speech.


1418
01:09:44.417 --> 01:09:46.085
Exactly.

1419
01:09:48.171 --> 01:09:52.675
But since it's tradition, I feel
obliged to carry the torch, so to speak.


1420
01:09:52.717 --> 01:09:55.595
Now, this year you've
chosen me to be Pere Noel,


1421
01:09:55.637 --> 01:09:57.222
"the ultimate father figure,"

1422
01:09:57.263 --> 01:09:59.891
as a friend of mine once said.

1423
01:09:59.933 --> 01:10:01.613
Because at Christmas,
you know, as parents,


1424
01:10:01.643 --> 01:10:03.895
we're busier
than ever, aren't we?


1425
01:10:03.937 --> 01:10:06.564
You know, it's a time of year
when our love for them


1426
01:10:06.606 --> 01:10:08.441
really shines.

1427
01:10:08.483 --> 01:10:10.777
It's a time when we remember

1428
01:10:10.819 --> 01:10:13.404
just how special that bond is.

1429
01:10:16.241 --> 01:10:20.662
I haven't always been
a perfect man or perfect father,


1430
01:10:20.703 --> 01:10:23.456
but having kids has been
the greatest honor of my life,


1431
01:10:23.498 --> 01:10:27.961
and if I ever accomplish anything on
this Earth, it will have been that,


1432
01:10:28.002 --> 01:10:32.715
so I would like to raise
a toast to my family, my girls,


1433
01:10:32.757 --> 01:10:35.176
my everything...

1434
01:10:35.218 --> 01:10:38.972
and to you and yours,
wherever they may be.


1435
01:10:39.013 --> 01:10:40.306
Cheers!

1436
01:10:40.348 --> 01:10:42.767
Cheers!

1437
01:10:45.395 --> 01:10:47.063
Whoo, whoo!

1438
01:10:47.105 --> 01:10:48.898
Cheers, you guys.

1439
01:10:53.862 --> 01:10:55.572
- Dad!
- Hey, how are y'all?


1440
01:10:55.613 --> 01:10:57.657
- How are ya?
- You did great, Dad.


1441
01:10:57.699 --> 01:10:59.784
Merry Chr... Thank you.
I practiced in the garage.


1442
01:10:59.826 --> 01:11:01.494
I didn't want to tell anybody.

1443
01:11:01.536 --> 01:11:04.414
You can't have any of that.

1444
01:11:04.455 --> 01:11:06.124
Okay.

1445
01:11:06.166 --> 01:11:07.834
Okay, uh...

1446
01:11:08.960 --> 01:11:10.461
Dad. No.

1447
01:11:10.503 --> 01:11:11.880
That's so strong.

1448
01:11:11.921 --> 01:11:12.839
Uh...

1449
01:11:12.881 --> 01:11:15.675
Okay, okay, Everett.

1450
01:11:15.717 --> 01:11:18.136
I wanted to say
something to you and...


1451
01:11:18.178 --> 01:11:20.597
Hey. What are you doing
all the way out here?


1452
01:11:20.638 --> 01:11:23.516
Eh, nothing.

1453
01:11:23.558 --> 01:11:25.185
Are you rehearsing?

1454
01:11:25.226 --> 01:11:27.562
No.

1455
01:11:27.604 --> 01:11:29.230
Maybe.

1456
01:11:29.272 --> 01:11:30.565
Okay, fine.

1457
01:11:30.607 --> 01:11:33.693
You and Jennifer got in my head.

1458
01:11:33.735 --> 01:11:38.031
And... that speech
from Everett...


1459
01:11:38.072 --> 01:11:41.034
This is just such
an important night, and...


1460
01:11:41.075 --> 01:11:44.430
it's my last chance to tell him before I leave
tomorrow, and I don't want to mess it up.


1461
01:11:44.454 --> 01:11:46.539
So speak from the heart.

1462
01:11:46.581 --> 01:11:49.417
Listen, I was wrong, okay?

1463
01:11:49.459 --> 01:11:51.377
Don't think so much.

1464
01:11:51.419 --> 01:11:53.546
<i>Now</i> you tell me.

1465
01:11:53.588 --> 01:11:55.715
Campbell...

1466
01:11:55.757 --> 01:11:57.759
who wouldn't love you?

1467
01:12:01.804 --> 01:12:04.182
I just...

1468
01:12:04.224 --> 01:12:06.684
Once I tell him,
everything's going to change...


1469
01:12:06.726 --> 01:12:08.603
For the better.

1470
01:12:08.645 --> 01:12:10.688
Yeah, I hope so.

1471
01:12:10.730 --> 01:12:13.900
Jackson, you were
supposed to bring her back.


1472
01:12:13.942 --> 01:12:16.778
I am now the rescue party
for the rescue party.


1473
01:12:18.321 --> 01:12:19.572
So, Campbell,

1474
01:12:19.614 --> 01:12:21.157
there's sort of
a lull over there.


1475
01:12:21.199 --> 01:12:23.284
I think now
might be a good time.


1476
01:12:27.497 --> 01:12:30.124
Yeah. Okay.

1477
01:12:30.166 --> 01:12:31.376
Yes.

1478
01:12:31.417 --> 01:12:33.044
Yeah.

1479
01:12:33.086 --> 01:12:34.295
I'm ready.

1480
01:12:35.797 --> 01:12:37.423
- Cool.
- You got this.


1481
01:12:37.465 --> 01:12:38.800
Yep.

1482
01:12:42.804 --> 01:12:44.973
Why am I so nervous?

1483
01:12:45.014 --> 01:12:46.933
Because you love her too.

1484
01:12:48.643 --> 01:12:49.936
Aw.

1485
01:12:54.440 --> 01:12:56.317
- Ooh, hey there.
- Hi.


1486
01:12:56.359 --> 01:12:58.528
All right, so...

1487
01:12:58.570 --> 01:13:00.029
what do you think of Sorrento?

1488
01:13:00.071 --> 01:13:03.950
Uh, compared to...
London, Paris?


1489
01:13:03.992 --> 01:13:06.578
Yeah, it's a special place,
that's for sure.


1490
01:13:06.619 --> 01:13:08.288
I'm sad I have
to leave tomorrow.


1491
01:13:08.329 --> 01:13:10.039
We feel the same way.

1492
01:13:10.081 --> 01:13:11.749
Got enough for your article?

1493
01:13:11.791 --> 01:13:15.295
Uh, actually,
I was hoping to talk to you,


1494
01:13:15.336 --> 01:13:18.965
you know, kid to Pere Noel.

1495
01:13:19.007 --> 01:13:22.343
Uh... yeah, of course.

1496
01:13:22.385 --> 01:13:24.470
- What's up?
- Um...


1497
01:13:24.512 --> 01:13:28.474
So, Everett, uh...

1498
01:13:28.516 --> 01:13:30.852
tonight in your speech,

1499
01:13:30.894 --> 01:13:35.023
you said that being a father was
the greatest honor of your life.


1500
01:13:35.064 --> 01:13:38.193
- Yeah.
- Yeah. And, um...


1501
01:13:38.234 --> 01:13:40.528
Dad, Campbell! We ran
into some fellow reporters


1502
01:13:40.570 --> 01:13:42.280
all the way from Mississippi!

1503
01:13:42.322 --> 01:13:44.574
- Oh!
- Pere Noel, if we could just get a few photos


1504
01:13:44.616 --> 01:13:46.659
of you and your family.

1505
01:13:46.701 --> 01:13:48.661
- Do you mind?
- Um...


1506
01:13:48.703 --> 01:13:50.497
Then we'll finish
our chat later?


1507
01:13:50.538 --> 01:13:52.165
- Yeah. Yeah, okay.
- Okay.


1508
01:13:52.207 --> 01:13:55.043
- Girls, what is all this?
- Oh, regional exposure, Mom.


1509
01:13:55.084 --> 01:13:56.878
Come on, get in the picture.

1510
01:13:56.920 --> 01:13:58.898
Yeah, actually, if you can stand
right next to Pere Noel.


1511
01:13:58.922 --> 01:14:00.089
Oh, yeah.

1512
01:14:02.592 --> 01:14:04.719
- Campbell.
- Oh, no, this is great.


1513
01:14:04.761 --> 01:14:06.262
Just the family's all we need.

1514
01:14:06.304 --> 01:14:08.139
All right.

1515
01:14:08.181 --> 01:14:10.058
Everybody look here.

1516
01:14:10.099 --> 01:14:13.186
All right, get together
and say, "Hot chocolate!"


1517
01:14:13.228 --> 01:14:15.230
Hot chocolate!

1518
01:14:15.271 --> 01:14:18.233
Yeah, the mayor did a good job.

1519
01:14:21.778 --> 01:14:23.613
So sorry, I'll be right back.

1520
01:14:29.077 --> 01:14:31.412
Hey, slow down!
Where are you going?


1521
01:14:31.454 --> 01:14:34.707
- I need to go home.
- Okay, well then, give me a minute, I'll go with you.


1522
01:14:34.749 --> 01:14:36.584
No, I'm...

1523
01:14:36.626 --> 01:14:38.878
I'm going home.

1524
01:14:38.920 --> 01:14:40.129
I'm sorry.

1525
01:14:40.171 --> 01:14:42.298
This was a huge mistake.

1526
01:14:42.340 --> 01:14:45.343
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.
What happened?


1527
01:14:45.385 --> 01:14:47.554
- What did he say?
- I didn't tell him, okay?


1528
01:14:47.595 --> 01:14:51.391
- Oh, Campbell.
- And I ask that you please don't either.


1529
01:14:51.432 --> 01:14:54.269
I just... I don't know
what I was thinking.


1530
01:14:54.310 --> 01:14:57.438
I have a family back in Dallas,
a great family, actually,


1531
01:14:57.480 --> 01:15:00.441
and, you know, maybe Everett not
coming back and not changing things


1532
01:15:00.483 --> 01:15:02.235
was for the best.

1533
01:15:02.277 --> 01:15:05.321
He left things alone, and maybe
I need to do the same thing.


1534
01:15:05.363 --> 01:15:07.240
Campbell.

1535
01:15:07.282 --> 01:15:10.201
Campbell!
Will you please just wait?


1536
01:15:10.243 --> 01:15:12.245
You need to let me go, Jackson.

1537
01:15:12.287 --> 01:15:14.789
This is your family,
your choice,


1538
01:15:14.831 --> 01:15:16.541
but you're leaving behind
such a gift.


1539
01:15:16.583 --> 01:15:18.168
It's so much more complicated
than that.


1540
01:15:18.209 --> 01:15:20.587
Of course it's complicated,
it's family.


1541
01:15:20.628 --> 01:15:21.921
I get it.

1542
01:15:21.963 --> 01:15:24.424
But they obviously
care about you.


1543
01:15:24.465 --> 01:15:26.176
Maybe if you just
told them the truth.


1544
01:15:26.217 --> 01:15:28.761
Maybe not all family
is meant to be.


1545
01:15:28.803 --> 01:15:30.430
Yes.

1546
01:15:30.471 --> 01:15:32.807
But can you honestly spend
the rest of your life


1547
01:15:32.849 --> 01:15:34.350
knowing what you left
behind here?


1548
01:15:46.404 --> 01:15:48.406
Campbell, hi, it's me again.

1549
01:15:48.448 --> 01:15:50.408
Uh, merry Christmas.

1550
01:15:50.450 --> 01:15:51.993
We, uh, missed you last night,

1551
01:15:52.035 --> 01:15:54.204
and I was just calling to see
if you're all right


1552
01:15:54.245 --> 01:15:57.832
and to let you know that the offer
for Christmas breakfast still stands.


1553
01:15:57.874 --> 01:16:00.084
Um, give us a call.

1554
01:16:00.126 --> 01:16:01.336
Bye.

1555
01:16:01.377 --> 01:16:03.296
She'll call.

1556
01:16:03.338 --> 01:16:05.590
I don't know,
maybe she finished her story.


1557
01:16:05.632 --> 01:16:08.510
I just feel bad for the girls. I mean,
they really took a liking to her.


1558
01:16:08.551 --> 01:16:13.389
I did too. I mean, do you really think
she would leave without saying goodbye?


1559
01:16:13.431 --> 01:16:15.141
Hey, it's Jackson.

1560
01:16:15.183 --> 01:16:17.602
- In the kitchen.
- Is it her?


1561
01:16:17.644 --> 01:16:19.062
Is she here?!

1562
01:16:19.103 --> 01:16:21.940
Merry Christmas,
Bergeron family.


1563
01:16:21.981 --> 01:16:24.067
- Oh, it's just you.
- Be nice.


1564
01:16:24.108 --> 01:16:27.862
It's okay, I get it. Campbell was a
very special person, I'd be sad too.


1565
01:16:27.904 --> 01:16:31.115
Luckily for you, though,
you don't have to be.


1566
01:16:31.157 --> 01:16:34.285
- Oh! Hey!
- Merry Christmas!


1567
01:16:34.327 --> 01:16:36.955
Merry Christmas!

1568
01:16:36.996 --> 01:16:38.873
Hello!

1569
01:16:38.915 --> 01:16:41.125
- Hello.
- See?


1570
01:16:41.167 --> 01:16:43.354
I told everyone you wouldn't
leave without saying goodbye.


1571
01:16:43.378 --> 01:16:45.380
- Never!
- We were worried you ran off.


1572
01:16:45.421 --> 01:16:48.341
And miss all this? No way.

1573
01:16:48.383 --> 01:16:50.468
I just couldn't come
to Christmas morning


1574
01:16:50.510 --> 01:16:53.972
without getting
some presents, and, uh...


1575
01:16:54.013 --> 01:16:56.349
my story is far from over.

1576
01:16:59.143 --> 01:17:02.230
Oh, and if anyone's wondering
if the big-box store out on I-10


1577
01:17:02.272 --> 01:17:06.151
is open at 2 a.m.
on Christmas Eve... it is.


1578
01:17:06.192 --> 01:17:08.069
Come on, now. Let's eat.

1579
01:17:08.111 --> 01:17:09.612
Give me those!

1580
01:17:09.654 --> 01:17:11.739
- Oh!
- Merry Christmas.


1581
01:17:11.781 --> 01:17:12.907
Thank you.

1582
01:17:14.534 --> 01:17:16.327
All right, girls,
put those under the tree,


1583
01:17:16.369 --> 01:17:18.204
and, uh, yeah, Jackson,
grab a seat.


1584
01:17:18.246 --> 01:17:19.956
Campbell, grab a seat.

1585
01:17:22.667 --> 01:17:25.336
- Juice!
- -All right, grab one and pass it down.


1586
01:17:25.378 --> 01:17:27.338
- Thank you.
- Gravy's on the side.


1587
01:17:33.636 --> 01:17:35.972
They're beautiful!
Thank you.


1588
01:17:36.014 --> 01:17:39.350
- You're welcome.
- Okay, so, last but not least...


1589
01:17:39.392 --> 01:17:43.062
Okay.
Uh... Mary-Margaret.


1590
01:17:43.104 --> 01:17:44.856
Oh, for me?

1591
01:17:44.898 --> 01:17:45.898
Yes.

1592
01:17:47.817 --> 01:17:50.737
For your budding
influencer career.


1593
01:17:52.363 --> 01:17:54.991
Seriously? Oh, my goodness.

1594
01:17:55.033 --> 01:17:57.535
I love it. Thank you!

1595
01:17:57.577 --> 01:17:59.370
Oh!

1596
01:17:59.412 --> 01:18:01.789
I thought you might.

1597
01:18:01.831 --> 01:18:02.874
Thank you so much.

1598
01:18:02.916 --> 01:18:04.626
Amelia.

1599
01:18:10.715 --> 01:18:12.509
A place to put your thoughts.

1600
01:18:13.968 --> 01:18:15.345
I have a lot of thoughts.

1601
01:18:17.388 --> 01:18:20.642
Uh, okay, and, Jennifer.

1602
01:18:20.683 --> 01:18:22.519
- One for you.
- Oh, wow, me too?


1603
01:18:22.560 --> 01:18:24.812
- Mm-hmm.
- Thank you.


1604
01:18:30.151 --> 01:18:32.070
It's our saying!

1605
01:18:32.111 --> 01:18:34.614
Yeah, well,
he shared your story with me,


1606
01:18:34.656 --> 01:18:37.116
and I was... inspired.

1607
01:18:37.158 --> 01:18:39.911
Oh, thank you so much.

1608
01:18:39.953 --> 01:18:41.412
Look at that.

1609
01:18:41.454 --> 01:18:43.122
You're good at this.

1610
01:18:43.164 --> 01:18:45.250
That is so sweet!

1611
01:18:45.291 --> 01:18:46.626
And, um...

1612
01:18:48.169 --> 01:18:51.172
Uh... Everett, yours is

1613
01:18:51.214 --> 01:18:53.174
the only one I didn't buy.

1614
01:19:12.318 --> 01:19:13.319
You can't be.

1615
01:19:13.361 --> 01:19:15.405
She...

1616
01:19:15.446 --> 01:19:17.782
my baby girl had darker hair

1617
01:19:17.824 --> 01:19:20.118
and a little crooked tooth.

1618
01:19:20.160 --> 01:19:21.870
Yeah, right in the front.

1619
01:19:26.457 --> 01:19:27.876
Alice?

1620
01:19:32.338 --> 01:19:34.132
I should have told you
the truth sooner,


1621
01:19:34.174 --> 01:19:36.176
but I needed...

1622
01:19:36.217 --> 01:19:38.303
I thought...

1623
01:19:38.344 --> 01:19:39.888
Everett.

1624
01:19:44.142 --> 01:19:46.102
Campbell, I'm so sorry.

1625
01:19:46.144 --> 01:19:48.104
Mama, what... what was it?

1626
01:19:50.148 --> 01:19:52.775
- Is she crying?
- It's okay.


1627
01:19:52.817 --> 01:19:54.944
No, it's fine.
I'm fine. I just, um...


1628
01:19:54.986 --> 01:19:56.905
- Campbell.
- We should get going anyway.


1629
01:19:58.740 --> 01:20:02.243
I... I have loved
every minute of my time here,


1630
01:20:02.285 --> 01:20:03.953
and all of you are, uh...

1631
01:20:03.995 --> 01:20:05.788
Wait, hang on.

1632
01:20:10.418 --> 01:20:12.962
Don't go.

1633
01:20:13.004 --> 01:20:14.756
What's this?

1634
01:20:14.797 --> 01:20:17.217
It's a gift, for you.

1635
01:20:20.637 --> 01:20:23.973
When I left,
I thought I was protecting you.


1636
01:20:24.015 --> 01:20:25.642
I thought it was
the right thing to do,


1637
01:20:25.683 --> 01:20:27.519
and I wanted you to know it

1638
01:20:27.560 --> 01:20:29.354
and to know how much
I missed you.


1639
01:20:29.395 --> 01:20:31.898
And so I sent some letters.

1640
01:20:33.441 --> 01:20:35.318
But we moved
and we changed our name.


1641
01:20:35.360 --> 01:20:36.569
- Yeah.
- Yeah.


1642
01:20:36.611 --> 01:20:38.321
And, uh,
when the letters came back,


1643
01:20:38.363 --> 01:20:40.156
I...

1644
01:20:40.198 --> 01:20:43.368
bought a notebook,
and I wrote in that instead,


1645
01:20:43.409 --> 01:20:47.038
everything that I was thinking,
everything that I was feeling,


1646
01:20:47.080 --> 01:20:52.085
all the regret and sorrow
and apologies and...


1647
01:20:52.126 --> 01:20:53.920
I wrote every day.

1648
01:20:53.962 --> 01:20:57.006
It's a lifetime
of days spent missing you


1649
01:20:57.048 --> 01:20:58.299
and loving you.

1650
01:21:12.313 --> 01:21:14.232
I thought you didn't want me.

1651
01:21:14.274 --> 01:21:17.193
No. Never.

1652
01:21:17.235 --> 01:21:19.279
I am so sorry.

1653
01:21:21.781 --> 01:21:26.244
I just... I can't believe
that you're really here.


1654
01:21:26.286 --> 01:21:28.246
I can't believe it, either.

1655
01:21:29.789 --> 01:21:32.208
Jennifer, you were
in on this, weren't you?


1656
01:21:32.250 --> 01:21:36.004
Yes.
But I had help from Jackson.


1657
01:21:36.045 --> 01:21:38.673
What can I say, I love to keep
the town family records complete.


1658
01:21:38.715 --> 01:21:40.925
Uh-huh.

1659
01:21:40.967 --> 01:21:44.304
Um, could somebody please
explain what's going on?


1660
01:21:44.345 --> 01:21:45.930
Yeah, why is everyone crying?

1661
01:21:45.972 --> 01:21:48.016
Well, uh, girls,

1662
01:21:48.057 --> 01:21:52.020
uh, years ago,
I had another daughter,


1663
01:21:52.061 --> 01:21:53.980
your older sister.

1664
01:21:55.481 --> 01:21:58.776
And Campbell...

1665
01:21:58.818 --> 01:22:01.446
- Wait, she's our sister?
- I knew it!


1666
01:22:01.488 --> 01:22:03.698
- You did not!
- I had a hunch.


1667
01:22:03.740 --> 01:22:06.075
Oh, a hunch!

1668
01:22:06.117 --> 01:22:08.203
Okay, so I'm not the oldest?

1669
01:22:08.244 --> 01:22:10.121
I guess not.

1670
01:22:10.163 --> 01:22:12.916
Wait, so if you're our sister,
then that means...


1671
01:22:17.462 --> 01:22:18.922
That's a great idea.

1672
01:22:21.674 --> 01:22:24.761
The secret ingredient.

1673
01:22:24.802 --> 01:22:27.180
We only share it with family.

1674
01:22:27.222 --> 01:22:30.058
- Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas.


1675
01:22:31.893 --> 01:22:33.895
Oh, I gotta get a piece of this.

1676
01:22:33.937 --> 01:22:37.148
Come on, now.

1677
01:22:37.190 --> 01:22:38.733
Oh, Jackson, come in.

1678
01:22:38.775 --> 01:22:41.361
Come in.

1679
01:22:41.402 --> 01:22:44.656
- Come on in! Come on!
- All right.


1680
01:22:44.697 --> 01:22:46.449
All right, merry Christmas on 3.

1681
01:22:46.491 --> 01:22:48.159
1, 2, 3!

1682
01:22:48.201 --> 01:22:50.203
Merry Christmas!

1683
01:22:50.245 --> 01:22:52.956
Yeah, that's a good one.

1684
01:22:52.997 --> 01:22:57.126
<i>Ever since that fateful Christmas,
I get asked a lot of things.</i>


1685
01:22:57.168 --> 01:23:00.046
<i>"What did it feel like
to meet your father?"</i>


1686
01:23:00.088 --> 01:23:04.133
<i>"Are your sisters
really that cool?"</i>


1687
01:23:04.175 --> 01:23:06.594
<i>"What made you go back
on Christmas morning?"</i>


1688
01:23:06.636 --> 01:23:09.222
<i>And "Is Jackson
as cute as he sounds?"</i>


1689
01:23:11.015 --> 01:23:12.767
<i>And all those
are fair questions,</i>


1690
01:23:12.809 --> 01:23:16.855
<i>but the question I get asked
the most often is,</i>


1691
01:23:16.896 --> 01:23:19.357
<i>"What happened next?"</i>

1692
01:23:19.399 --> 01:23:21.442
<i>What happened after my first</i>

